(1980, 'Make-A-Wish Surprise at GR Airport', 'Bo is a 10-year-old boy who is a huge Star Wars fan. He and his family are on Southwest Flight #551 at 3:35pm out of GRR. The family will likely be arriving between 1-130pm so we would ask that the â€˜charactersâ€™ come around 12:30 to change over and get them up to the gate. There will be GVSU students there to surprise Bo upon his arrival at the airport. I think we will stage them near the Southwest ticket counter as Bo and his family check in. I have reserved our airport International Room for characters to change over.We can lock this after they are done so everything will be safe. This room is directly next to our police office and just past the west restrooms in the main grand hall area where people meet & greet passengers. Additionally, have characters bring in their parking tickets and I will validate parking. I can also have refreshments available. ', '2017-02-03', NULL, 'Grand Rapids', 'MI', '', 0, 1, 1, NULL, NULL),
(1981, 'DeVos Children\'s Hospital visit', 'DeVos Children\'s Hospital', '2017-03-01', NULL, 'Grand Rapids', 'MI', '', 0, 1, 1, NULL, NULL),
(1982, 'Child\'s NF1/Cancer Fight Fundraiser', 'This is personal. This is a family friend of ours from the local, crunchy parenting groups. Her little toddler is fighting NF1/cancer. \r\n\r\nSaturday, February 25th, 4pm-8pm (Report time around 3:30ish or whenever you can get there, don\'t have to stay the whole time, but I probably will be.)\r\nContact Name: Me\r\nContact Phone Number: Mine is (616) 304-9937\r\nContact Email: parkindj@hotmail.com \r\nVenue: Grandville Cummings Elementary\r\nVenue address: 4261 Schoolcraft Street Southwest, Grand Rapids, MI 49534\r\nEvent Start: Feb. 25th, 2017\r\nEvent Website: https://www.youcaring.com/crew-berens-656223\r\nExpected number of attendees: No idea\r\nRequested number of characters: Whoever shows up, I will be going for sure. Erin will be there with the kids probably.\r\nRequested character types: Anyone!\r\nSecure changing/staging area: **Still working on this** do not have it confirmed yet but there will be room.\r\nComments: People will pay to get in, there will be silent auction things available. We will just be there doing photos, hanging out, etc.\r\nFood? Still working on that one........\r\n\r\nFrom his Momma, Hilary Berens: \r\n          \"At 12 months old we first heard the word â€˜Neurofibromatosisâ€™ from our pediatrician.\r\nAt age 13 months old we found out our son Crew had a tumor near his brain on his trigeminal nerve.\r\nAt age 13 months Crew was formally diagnosed with Neurofibromatosis 1 (NF1).\r\n          At age 26 months a MRI scan showed many new & growing tumors in his mouth, tongue, cheek, and neck. These tumors can continue to grow all over his body and on his nerves. We are unable to biopsy any of his tumors at this time, and it is possible for them to turn in to cancer. The shape of Crewâ€™s tongue is now being affected by the tumors. Sometimes when he speaks his tongue favors one side of his mouth. His right cheek is now noticeably larger than the left. Tumors running along his nerves and carotid artery are visibly seen on the right side of his neck. Due to the tumor on the trigeminal nerve, every time when he chews food red flushing occurs on his right cheek that sometimes goes into his ear, eye lid and hairline. Sometimes when his skin flushes his right eye will water.\r\n          Putting pride aside, I need to ask for help. We have three young children, Crew & Cecelia are 26 months old and our daughter Everly is 4 months old. I have my Bachelorâ€™s in Social Work and was a full time career woman until we were blessed with our twins. I became a proud Stay at Home Mom and we changed our lifestyle to manage and maintain on one income. My husband Scott is a very hard working man. He is a full time Associate Chemist at Gerber Baby Foods in Fremont, MI. He works 12hr days, 1 hour commutes back and forth, to provide for our family. We live life frugally to make sure our one income meets our needs. However, money is tight and as the medical expenses add up it will only make things more difficult.\"\r\n', '2017-02-25', NULL, 'Grand Rapids', 'MI', '', 0, 1, 1, NULL, NULL),
(1983, 'Byron Center Rec. Comic-Con ', 'The 2017 date for the second annual Byron Rec Comic Con has been set as Saturday, February 4th! The first Saturday in February again, we are also keeping the same time: 10am-4pm. We will be improving some things and working to make this one even better than the first year. As happy as we were with the first year, there are definitely improvements we can make to provide an even better con to the community. It will also remain without an admission fee. We welcome everyone to visit, shop, cosplay, and enjoy.\r\n\r\nLast year was a successful event.\r\nNo set time for anyone to be there. Come troop and have a good time.\r\nMore up-dates will be posted.\r\nI will EC this event. Thank you. Sparra', '2017-02-04', NULL, 'Byron Center', 'MI', '', 0, 0, 1, NULL, NULL),
(1984, 'Kalamazoo Polar Plunge', 'The Kalamazoo and Calhoun Plunge takes place February 11, 2017 at Bell\'s Eccentric Cafe. Registration starts at 9:30 a.m. with the plunge at 10:30 a.m. The After Splash Bash will start immediately after the last plunger.\r\n\r\nMichigan will be having 25 Polar Plunges in 2017. Polar Plunges are a Law Enforcement Torch Run (LETR) event. LETR is one of the largest grassroots fundraisers for Special Olympics globally. LETR consists of officers from both Law Enforcement and Corrections who raise funds and create awareness for SOMI year round.\r\n\r\nBy participating in a Polar Plunge around the state you are helping to raise funds for over 23,000 athletes who participate in Special Olympics Michigan. Special Olympics Michigan is a year round program offering sports for those with intellectual disabilities. Although sports are the \"vehicle,\" the ultimate goal of Special Olympics is to help persons with intellectual disabilities participate and receive respect as members of their communities.', '2017-02-11', NULL, 'Kalamazoo', 'MI', '', 0, 0, 1, NULL, NULL),
